# Caddy terminates TLS and proxies to the Node app (service name `web`, port 8080).
#
# Set CADDY_DOMAIN to your public hostname (e.g. portfolio.shibleyrecords.com).
# Ports 80 and 443 must be published on the host. Caddy obtains/renews Let's Encrypt certs automatically.
#
# Local try: CADDY_DOMAIN=localhost (Caddy uses an internal certificate for HTTPS on localhost).

{$CADDY_DOMAIN} {
	reverse_proxy web:8080
}
